1
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:00,000
The Story of Ming Lan

2
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,580
Episode 44

3
00:01:03,570 --> 00:01:04,240
Please.

4
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:06,800
Thank you, Nanny.

5
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:13,600
Good wine.

6
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,160
Enjoy it.

7
00:01:15,160 --> 00:01:15,640
Nanny.

8
00:01:16,440 --> 00:01:18,560
you're too courteous.

9
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:21,040
You are treating us way too good.

10
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:23,080
You are the nanny of Master,

11
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:25,400
You are in a high position,

12
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:27,800
yet you still treat us with some drink.

13
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:29,760
I really feel flattered.

14
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:31,160
Isn't that right?

15
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:33,520
I don't care about positions.

16
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,640
Young Master Ye and I

17
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:37,480
have never put any importance

18
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,800
to those so-called seniority rules.

19
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,880
You can say so,

20
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:45,200
but we're

21
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,560
still working for the inner courtyard.

22
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:47,920
No matter how good Master is,

23
00:01:48,162 --> 00:01:49,317
we are out of the master's reach.

24
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:51,400
Big Madam is our boss.

25
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,120
Big Madam

26
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,040
isn't as resolute as Master.

27
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:57,480
Look at how chaotic

28
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,640
the kitchen has become.

29
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,240
She doesn't even ask about it.

30
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,520
Indeed.

31
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:04,760
Today, Rong

32
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:06,440
wants to eat swamp eel,

33
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,040
I then went to the kitchen to ask if there was any.

34
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,000
Before I even entered,

35
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,520
I've already heard Nanny Lai yelling.

36
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:16,560
Her words were really unbearable.

37
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:18,720
Even a woman from the countryside like me

38
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:19,600
felt embarrassed.

39
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:21,880
And this person even came from

40
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:24,000
the marquis house.

41
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,760
She claims that she's a person

42
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,800
who has attended to Big Madam

43
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,520
of the marquis hourse,

44
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:33,520
but I don't think so.

45
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:36,280
Those dowry servants that Big Madam

46
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,760
brought with her from Qin Manor

47
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,920
were mostly

48
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:40,520
gone or dead.

49
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:42,080
Only Nanny Xiang

50
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:43,040
is by her side.

51
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:44,920
I am really puzzled.

52
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,560
What is the background

53
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,000
of this Nanny Lai?

54
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,800
So barbaric.

55
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:53,040
I heard that

56
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,000
she came here

57
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,760
with Nanny Xiang's help.

58
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,600
Because she has

59
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,560
served longer than us,

60
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:02,040
hence, she was able to look so decent.

61
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:02,920
Let me tell you,

62
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:04,000
she keeps showing off,

63
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,360
that she's a trusted maid of Big Madam.

64
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,920
What's to be proud of this?

65
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,400
In my opinion,

66
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,000
you two

67
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,960
are not worse than her.

68
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,480
Why must you two have lower positon than her?

69
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,920
We work for the fourth and fifth house,

70
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:23,700
who are not as prestigious

71
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:24,680
as the main house.

72
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:27,920
Speaking of this,

73
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:31,100
before going to the western expedition,

74
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,520
do you know

75
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:33,840
how Young Master

76
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:34,960
was able to become a general overnight?

77
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,550
Wasn't it because he was meritorious

78
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:38,560
for saving the emperor?

79
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,880
The current emperor

80
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:45,560
was still an unfavored one.

81
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:48,150
Afterwards, there was a palace siege

82
00:03:48,150 --> 00:03:49,240
to usurp the throne.

83
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,400
It was Young Master

84
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,920
who risked his life to escort His Majesty,

85
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:56,320
and fought all out against the rebels,

86
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:58,800
hence, he has his current prestige.

87
00:03:59,754 --> 00:04:01,040
If that time,

88
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,800
Young Master was afraid of dying

89
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:05,920
and just hid in Yuzhou to preserve his life,

90
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,400
can he have such success today?

91
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:09,150
Can he have this enormous wealth

92
00:04:09,150 --> 00:04:09,960
and high status now?

93
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,320
What Nanny means is...

94
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:16,200
Every time a new emperor ascends,

95
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:17,120
the ministers are changed.

96
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:20,080
If you two can unit

97
00:04:20,080 --> 00:04:22,120
to pull down Nanny Lai,

98
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:25,280
a thorn in Big Madam's side,

99
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:27,720
will she treat you two unfairly?

100
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,880
You cowards.

101
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:39,720
Whether you do it or not,

102
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:42,040
I'm still the nanny of our master.

103
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,717
Who in this house

104
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,157
can have a position higher than me?

105
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:46,680
You don't

106
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:48,760
listen to the good words I say.

107
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:51,760
When bandits join a group,

108
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:53,520
they will show their loyalty and devotion first.

109
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,480
Fine.

110
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,200
You two are indeed

111
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,840
just suitable to drink wine in this garden,

112
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,520
What Nanny said is right.

113
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:16,440
Nanny said it right.

114
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,720
Yes, Nanny,

115
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:20,400
we remember your words.

116
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,012
Come, Nanny,

117
00:05:22,012 --> 00:05:23,480
let me give you a toast.

118
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:32,120
I caught something!

119
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,080
I've caught it! I've caught it!

120
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,280
Let me do it.

121
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:48,280
After catching plenty of fish,

122
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:49,840
we'll have something to eat with wines tonight.

123
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:59,120
Since I came to the capital

124
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,360
with elder Sister and Brother-in-law,

125
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:03,280
this has been my happiest day.

126
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,760
No need to restrain myself

127
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:06,120
and consider the opinion of those elders.

128
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:07,600
I also don't need to keep my head

129
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,800
from shaking when walking,

130
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,600
or showing my teeth when laughing,

131
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,200
as if I'm some demure lady.

132
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,400
Come here often then.

133
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,500
You're the only one left

134
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,720
that doesn't mind me being wild.

135
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,880
In the capital City,

136
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,200
all rich daughters

137
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,600
are courteous

138
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,640
before me,

139
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:25,520
but mocking me

140
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:26,880
as a country bumpkin behind my back?

141
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,760
Let alone fishing,

142
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,320
Even if I just talk a bit louder,

143
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:33,840
they will laugh at me.

144
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:36,080
Sometimes, I didn't even know

145
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:37,440
that they were laughing at me.

146
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,880
I even laughed with them.

147
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:42,320
You're also laughing at me?

148
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,840
The two of us can get along well.

149
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:48,280
You and a cousin of mine in our home province

150
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:51,800
are of similar age and personality.

151
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,600
She is also wild when she plays and runs.

152
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:58,560
She can climb trees to get bird's eggs

153
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,800
or dive into the river to catch toads.

154
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,160
She can do all those.

155
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:02,425
In our home province, she's the person

156
00:07:02,425 --> 00:07:03,400
that I'm able to get along with the most.

157
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,840
Once she comes to visit me,

158
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:07,520
I'll tell her to play with you.

159
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,040
The capital is almost killing me

160
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,320
with suffocating rules.

161
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:11,720
Don't know

162
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:12,560
if I can still live

163
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,360
until your cousin arrives.

164
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,600
It's indeed a good thing

165
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,320
that brother-in-law of mine

166
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:18,360
became the emperor.

167
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,040
But it feels like shackles

168
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,000
have been placed on me.

169
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,400
If I make any mistake,

170
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,960
I would be bringing trouble to my whole family.

171
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,640
Aristocratic families are indeed like that.

172
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,280
They are deeply entangled.

173
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,200
One committing a mistake

174
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,200
will affect everyone else.

175
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:34,800
Good thing,

176
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,240
you were married into the Zheng Family.

177
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:39,680
Your in-laws are all from reputable families.

178
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,920
As days pass by,

179
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,600
everyone will know

180
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,560
that you have a pure and kind temperament.

181
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,720
They will eventually accept you.

182
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,160
Xiaotao,

183
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,200
take these fish to the kitchen.

184
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:51,760
Let's just go around.

185
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,120
We haven't been to even a half of

186
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:53,840
this huge garden yet.

187
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:54,720
Sure!

188
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:01,280
In the kitchen,

189
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,080
I'm the one in charge after all.

190
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,920
I'm just getting a few of

191
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:05,800
these rotten leafy vegetables.

192
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,200
Do you have to comment so much?

193
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,960
Rotten leafy vegetables?

194
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:13,080
All these were raised and cared

195
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:13,840
for idling people

196
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:15,200
like us in the garden.

197
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:17,120
They are for the Miss Rong's soup.

198
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:17,550
Just for saying

199
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:18,600
that it's a rotten leafy vegetable,

200
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,560
you want to take it away?

201
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,560
Are you more respectable

202
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,720
than our Miss?

203
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:22,240
I...

204
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:24,720
Isn't it just a few wild vegetables?

205
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:25,840
If I eat yours,

206
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:26,840
I'll just get you

207
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,640
some to make it up.

208
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:30,560
Is it necessary to make a fuss like that?

209
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,794
Say,

210
00:08:31,794 --> 00:08:32,200
just let it go.

211
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:34,400
just for a few leafy vegetables,

212
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:35,600
Stop fighting.

213
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,440
Make it up?!

214
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,480
If Big Madam asks,

215
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,600
how would I explain it?

216
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,360
You know very clearly

217
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:44,200
that this is not about just a few wild vegetables.

218
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,800
Since you got in charge of the kitchen,

219
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:48,000
how many items have been converted to silver

220
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,040
and entered your pocket.

221
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:50,040
Can you explain those clearly?!

222
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:50,480
You...

223
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,000
stop using Big Madam to oppress me!

224
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,760
I didn't eat yours

225
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,760
or spend your money,

226
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:56,760
so why are you being hurt?

227
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,840
I think

228
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,080
you're just jealous

229
00:08:59,080 --> 00:08:59,840
because others are getting kickbacks

230
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,160
while you're not.

231
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,560
Getting agitated about it.

232
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:02,950
You've already gotten advantages

233
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:03,400
and you still pretend to be nice?!

234
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:03,960
I'll beat you flat!

235
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,680
Do you believe that?!

236
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,960
What are you doing?!

237
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,440
You people want to beat me up?!

238
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,920
Hit her until she dies! Get out! Leave!

239
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,120
Stinky brat!

240
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,080
Go away!

241
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:16,440
You are really so bold! You!

242
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,800
Stop! Stop!

243
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:22,960
You are the person I want to punch!

244
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,000
Stop!

245
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,040
Stop pulling me! Get off!

246
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,120
Did a thief enter your house?

247
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:29,321
No.

248
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:30,880
It must be the senior kitchen maids

249
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:31,880
fighting again.

250
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,600
Forget it.

251
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,720
Let's find a more peaceful place

252
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:35,400
to talk.

253
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,640
No, they are breaking things now.

254
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:37,840
Sister, you're not intervening?

255
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,240
I'll kill you!

256
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,440
You stinky brat!

257
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:54,800
I'll kill you!

258
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:56,960
Young Master! Young Master! We have trouble!

259
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,900
The people inside the inner courtyard kitchen

260
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:01,200
are fighting.

261
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:04,680
What happened?

262
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,480
I heard that it's about some wild vegetables.

263
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,800
Nanny Lai, Nanny Hua, Nanny Tian,

264
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:08,880
and a few more maidservants

265
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:10,000
are all fighting there!

266
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,160
Why are you telling me these?

267
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:18,000
Must I still meddle with

268
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,280
those trifle matters in the kitchen?

269
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:21,360
Where's Big Madam?

270
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,760
Tell her to go over there and take a look.

271
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:24,720
Big Madam doesn't dare to meddle.

272
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:26,520
She said that those are nannies sent

273
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,640
by the elders of the marquis house.

274
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,320
Then just forget it.

275
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,320
Is everything still okay?

276
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,440
It's fine, General.

277
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,040
You better go over and take a look.

278
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,720
What's there to look at?

279
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,850
A few elderly women are fighting

280
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:43,960
and I still have to meddle?

281
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:45,120
Just let them fight.

282
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:46,720
At most, let them trash the kitchen

283
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:47,600
and destroy its roof.

284
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,000
I'll just hire some people to rebuild it.

285
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:52,600
Let's just drink.

286
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,960
You, beat the drum!

287
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,360
Okay! Okay!

288
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:03,560
Right.

289
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:05,760
